Luka Koper d.d.  said revenue in the
first six-months advanced 3 percent from a year earlier as the
Slovenian port operator handled more cars.  Revenue advanced to 69.2 million euros ($84.7 million) from
67.2 million euros in the same period last year, the Koper,
Slovenia-based company said in a regulatory  statement  today.
Cargo handled by the port in the period increased 8 percent to 9
million tons, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
